    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Children and Youth to Join in Service for Others</strong>&mdash;In an effort to excuse themselves some say: &ldquo;My home duties, my children, claim my time and my means.&rdquo; Parents, your children should be your helping hand, increasing your power and ability to work for the Master. Children are the younger members of the Lord&apos;s family. They should be led to consecrate themselves to God, <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"486\"></span> whose they are by creation and by redemption. They should be taught that all their powers of body, mind, and soul are His. They should be trained to help in various lines of unselfish service. Do not allow your children to be hindrances. With you the children should share spiritual as well as physical burdens. By helping others they increase their own happiness and usefulness.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">5<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"7T 63.1\" data-link=\"117.338\">Ibid., 7:63</span>.</span></a></sup>",
