    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "In their early years children may be useful in God&apos;s work.... He will give them His grace and His Holy Spirit, that they may overcome impatience, fretfulness, and all sin. Jesus loves the children. He has blessings for them, and He loves to see them obedient to their parents. <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"487\"></span> He desires them to be His little missionaries, denying their own inclinations and desires for selfish pleasure to do service for Him; and this service is just as acceptable to God as is the service of grown-up children.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">8<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 11-17-1896\" data-link=\"821.15360\">The Review and Herald, November 17, 1896</span>.</span></a></sup>",
