    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "In this work, as in every other, skill is gained in the work itself. It is by training in the common duties of life and in ministry to the needy and suffering that efficiency is assured. Without this the best-meant efforts are often useless and even harmful. It is in the water, not on the land, that men learn to swim.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">18<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Ed 268.1\" data-link=\"29.1417\">Education, 268</span>.</span></a></sup>",
